@Vaer 

We have those aisles in our supermarkets, too, I just generally don't visit them. I don't drink sodas (alcohol is my unhealthy drink of choice, and I drink little of it these days, anyway), I only snack on nuts, olives or fruit, and if I buy cereal at all, it is always the very specific kind of muesli my wife likes best, and I navigate towards it on auto pilot, never looking at the other stuff in the same aisle. I'm a walking nightmare of the people whose job it is to make us buy more, more, more. I always have a shopping list on my phone and i stick to it, I know from experience what brands offer the best quality, and if I ever buy something new, it is based on its label (ingredients, place of origin, etc.) rather than some ad I saw or a promotion.

Obviously I am quite boring much of the time, too :D

@Andrzej 

