@Robert 

We have an individual number in Poland, PESEL, but it's not secret - e.g. when you are the CEO of a company, your PESEL is publicly listed. Also, there is very little anybody could do to hurt another person by using only their PESEL - without forging signatures or the like on top of it.

How does the Spanish NIE work?

@Jane Wheelaghan 

In Scotland, a lot of people know their 10-digit NHS identifier, which is called the Community Health Index (CHI). It's easy to remember, because six of the ten digits are your date of birth, so you only need to get four digits into your head. Anyone who's a frequent flyer with health services tends to acquire them subliminally, from the header on their appointment letters.
(You can tell someone's biological sex from the third digit of the extra four: men are odd and women are even. Make of that what you will.)

